article.description: Chante Black had 19 points, nine rebounds and four blocks to lead Duke to a 70-38 win over Florida State.
article.headline: Duke rips Seminoles for 23rd straight home win
article.linkText: Duke rips Florida State for 23rd straight home win
article.story:
DURHAM, N.C. (AP) -- Chante Black had 19 points, nine rebounds and four blocks to lead Duke (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to a 70-38 win over Florida State on Friday night.

Reserve Bridgette Mitchell added 10 points for Duke, which gave coach Joanne P. McCallie her first Atlantic Coast Conference win at home.

The Blue Devils took advantage of a horrendous shooting night for the Seminoles (11-6, 1-1) to pick up their 23rd straight home win, the longest active streak in the nation. Florida State shot 23.4 percent for the game.

The easy win was a tuneup for the Blue Devils, who travel to No. 4 Maryland on Monday for what will be their first big test in the ACC this season.

The Blue Devils took an early 12-10 lead -- 10 of those points coming from Black -- before Florida State went nearly six minutes without a bucket, allowing the Blue Devils (13-3, 2-0) to take control of the game.

The Seminoles played without leading scorer Tanae Davis-Cain, who averages 13.7 points per game, and top post player Britany Miller. Davis-Cain is suspended "for violation of team standards" and Miller is academically ineligible.

Antionette Howard was the Seminoles' leading scorer with eight points while Mara Freshour had 10 rebounds. Florida State's trouble scoring continued into the second half. The Seminoles needed 4 minutes, 57 seconds before Freshour scored their first bucket of the half.
